Depends on where the sentience/bipedial event was.
I placed it back about 4-8mya, so my canids predate wolves, and would have outcompeted any number of other regional canidae.
In my setting the question is irrelevant; feral wolves and domesticated dogs exist in the same manner that we humans still have chimps & gorillas.

Now...if you follow some magic event that allowed the earliest possible true wolves (0.5-0.25mya ago) to acquire the equivalent of a few million years of evolution rapidly, I see no reason you couldn't have the same branching effect.
A more recent branching would be ideal if you want a stronger emphasis on canid sensory traits, a less modern if you want a potential evolution that reduces olfactory capacity in exchange for increased visual/color acuity.

What they call loyalty is on a scale most humans would consider a deal with the devil, and given some European myths of wolves...
